                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d425">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.51/1849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Munro</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-11-01T12:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1927—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 4:24 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>311. Department’s 167, October 28, 5 p.m. The proposal to send Cumberland to make
                    a financial survey meets with the hearty approval of both President Diaz and the
                    representatives of the Liberal Party. Will the Department or the Government of
                    Nicaragua bear the expenses?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Munro</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
